Text.SourceString: Oh yeah, yeah! I heard about you.//You’re that new farmer from San Franciskyo, right?//<portrait=normal>Ah, that’s right! <Italic>Pokyo</>.//I’m <NPCName>Theo</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh yeah, yeah! I heard about you.//You’re that new farmer from San Franciskyo, right?//<portrait=normal>Ah, that’s right! <Italic>Pokyo</>.//I’m <NPCName>Theo</>.

Text.SourceString: Me? I’m from here. I fish for a living.
Text.LocalizedString: Me? I’m from here. I fish for a living.

Text.SourceString: There are so many microplastics in the sea.//<portrait=annoyed>You’d be surprised how much trash I can gather in just one day out fishing.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many microplastics in the sea.//<portrait=annoyed>You’d be surprised how much trash I can gather in just one day out fishing.

Text.SourceString: One time, I was walking past the recycling center when inspiration struck.//<portrait=concerned>What could I do to help? My heart was set, and that was it.//<portrait=happy>I stopped and hung out there for two days, writing a song about recyclables.
Text.LocalizedString: One time, I was walking past the recycling center when inspiration struck.//<portrait=concerned>What could I do to help? My heart was set, and that was it.//<portrait=happy>I stopped and hung out there for two days, writing a song about recyclables.

Text.SourceString: It goes: Who were you~ Plastic bottle~ Where did you come frooooom~ A lump of trash~ Dooooo doo doo dooooo doodooooo~
Text.LocalizedString: It goes: Who were you~ Plastic bottle~ Where did you come frooooom~ A lump of trash~ Dooooo doo doo dooooo doodooooo~

Text.SourceString: I might try my hand at gardening one of these days.//<portrait=happy>I bet it’s a great outlet for self-expression.//<portrait=normal>All I need is a little piece of land and some seeds from <NpcName>Sam</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I might try my hand at gardening one of these days.//<portrait=happy>I bet it’s a great outlet for self-expression.//<portrait=normal>All I need is a little piece of land and some seeds from <NpcName>Sam</>.

Text.SourceString: Now isn’t the time…//<portrait=happy>I’m waiting for my calling to farm before I start.//<portrait=normal>Won’t be too long… I can feel it coming on soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Now isn’t the time…//<portrait=happy>I’m waiting for my calling to farm before I start.//<portrait=normal>Won’t be too long… I can feel it coming on soon.

Text.SourceString: Oh, can you really tell?!//<portrait=happy>Yeah, I taught myself how to play the guitar and sing.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, can you really tell?!//<portrait=happy>Yeah, I taught myself how to play the guitar and sing.

Text.SourceString: I refuse to pay for one of those shallow classes.//<portrait=angry>They don't teach you how to express yourself authentically. All they care about is making pretty sounds.
Text.LocalizedString: I refuse to pay for one of those shallow classes.//<portrait=angry>They don't teach you how to express yourself authentically. All they care about is making pretty sounds.

Text.SourceString: In this day and age, people can be so greedy.//We're always chasing after more and more and more.//<portrait=sad>It’s sad, really.
Text.LocalizedString: In this day and age, people can be so greedy.//We're always chasing after more and more and more.//<portrait=sad>It’s sad, really.

Text.SourceString: Let me tell you something I learned, <PlayerName>$player</>.//People who are happy, they've got that glow 'cause they find joy in the little things, not from chasing the big bucks.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell you something I learned, <PlayerName>$player</>.//People who are happy, they've got that glow 'cause they find joy in the little things, not from chasing the big bucks.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I’ll buy a new boat someday. But trust me, it won't be the boat that puts a smile on my face.//<portrait=happy>It's all about that fishing life.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I’ll buy a new boat someday. But trust me, it won't be the boat that puts a smile on my face.//<portrait=happy>It's all about that fishing life.

Text.SourceString: We need to take time to know ourselves.//Knowing yourself is like having a long chat with a mirror, it's surprising how many arguments you can lose.
Text.LocalizedString: We need to take time to know ourselves.//Knowing yourself is like having a long chat with a mirror, it's surprising how many arguments you can lose.

Text.SourceString: Oh! I forgot!//<portrait=concerned>I’m meeting my friends at the community center today.//<portrait=sad>Oh, no, no. Hang on. That’s tomorrow!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! I forgot!//<portrait=concerned>I’m meeting my friends at the community center today.//<portrait=sad>Oh, no, no. Hang on. That’s tomorrow!

Text.SourceString: I don’t have a favorite kind of music. I like any song that’s made with love.//When I’m listening, all I hear is the love the creator put in.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t have a favorite kind of music. I like any song that’s made with love.//When I’m listening, all I hear is the love the creator put in.

Text.SourceString: What about you? What’s your favorite music genre?
Text.LocalizedString: What about you? What’s your favorite music genre?

Text.SourceString: The beach and the sea are my favorite places.//The sea is so peaceful, isn’t it? It shelters millions of lives, yet it remains so humble.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach and the sea are my favorite places.//The sea is so peaceful, isn’t it? It shelters millions of lives, yet it remains so humble.

Text.SourceString: I live with my sister and dad by the lake. It gets spooky at night.
Text.LocalizedString: I live with my sister and dad by the lake. It gets spooky at night.

Text.SourceString: Heh heh… Kidding. It doesn’t, I’m just messing with you.//<portrait=normal>But there are wild animals around here, so they might be responsible for any weird noises the townies hear.
Text.LocalizedString: Heh heh… Kidding. It doesn’t, I’m just messing with you.//<portrait=normal>But there are wild animals around here, so they might be responsible for any weird noises the townies hear.

Text.SourceString: There was a time I used to freak out about not having a 'real job' or taking the same beaten path as my sis.//<portrait=surprised>But hey, not anymore!
Text.LocalizedString: There was a time I used to freak out about not having a 'real job' or taking the same beaten path as my sis.//<portrait=surprised>But hey, not anymore!

Text.SourceString: I am who I am, and there’s nothing wrong with that.//<portrait=happy>People may call me boring, but I know myself better.//<portrait=normal>I’m not boring or unmotivated… I’m laid-back.
Text.LocalizedString: I am who I am, and there’s nothing wrong with that.//<portrait=happy>People may call me boring, but I know myself better.//<portrait=normal>I’m not boring or unmotivated… I’m laid-back.

Text.SourceString: I think we owe it to ourselves to be happy.//And the secret sauce? Just be cool with what you've got.
Text.LocalizedString: I think we owe it to ourselves to be happy.//And the secret sauce? Just be cool with what you've got.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, I'm not sure why I'm blabbing all this to you. It's like my mouth took the steering wheel and I'm just along for the ride.//<portrait=angry>Kinda  weird.
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, I'm not sure why I'm blabbing all this to you. It's like my mouth took the steering wheel and I'm just along for the ride.//<portrait=angry>Kinda  weird.

Text.SourceString: Anyone can catch legendary fish at sea with enough skill.//<portrait=normal>They’re hard to find, but not impossible.
Text.LocalizedString: Anyone can catch legendary fish at sea with enough skill.//<portrait=normal>They’re hard to find, but not impossible.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Sunny</> is a big name around here.//Dude used to chase down those legendary monster fish like it was his job!
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Sunny</> is a big name around here.//Dude used to chase down those legendary monster fish like it was his job!

Text.SourceString: I’m not actively hunting for legendary fish.//I don’t see the appeal.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not actively hunting for legendary fish.//I don’t see the appeal.

Text.SourceString: So what's your game plan for the weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: So what's your game plan for the weekend?

Text.SourceString: I sing live on weekends.//<portrait=happy>I don’t make much, but I can always use the tips.
Text.LocalizedString: I sing live on weekends.//<portrait=happy>I don’t make much, but I can always use the tips.

Text.SourceString: Gotta hand it to <NpcName>Betty</>, though.//She's out there making sure our feathered friends don't go hungry.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta hand it to <NpcName>Betty</>, though.//She's out there making sure our feathered friends don't go hungry.

Text.SourceString: Any big plans for the day?
Text.LocalizedString: Any big plans for the day?

Text.SourceString: My old man's a fisher, but he's hung up his fishing rod these days.//<portrait=concerned>Too old for the night wind, he says.
Text.LocalizedString: My old man's a fisher, but he's hung up his fishing rod these days.//<portrait=concerned>Too old for the night wind, he says.

Text.SourceString: He helps <NpcName>Sunny</> run the Beach Shack full-time now.
Text.LocalizedString: He helps <NpcName>Sunny</> run the Beach Shack full-time now.

Text.SourceString: Wealth isn’t everything, <PlayerName>$player</>. Don’t waste your life chasing it.
Text.LocalizedString: Wealth isn’t everything, <PlayerName>$player</>. Don’t waste your life chasing it.

Text.SourceString: Nice to see you stretching your legs!//<portrait=normal>Living on a big farm can be quite isolating.
Text.LocalizedString: Nice to see you stretching your legs!//<portrait=normal>Living on a big farm can be quite isolating.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be deep in thought.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be deep in thought.]

Text.SourceString: My sister is right, it isn’t about us being independent…//Living at home is a tradition in our family. It’s been like that for generations.
Text.LocalizedString: My sister is right, it isn’t about us being independent…//Living at home is a tradition in our family. It’s been like that for generations.

Text.SourceString: My uncles and aunts all lived at home until they were married.
Text.LocalizedString: My uncles and aunts all lived at home until they were married.

Text.SourceString: *[<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be deep in thought.]
Text.LocalizedString: *[<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be deep in thought.]

Text.SourceString: For a while, I tried making a living as a truck driver, but it can get pretty lonely on the road.
Text.LocalizedString: For a while, I tried making a living as a truck driver, but it can get pretty lonely on the road.

Text.SourceString: I guess being away from family for too long just isn’t for me.//<portrait=normal>The pay was good, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess being away from family for too long just isn’t for me.//<portrait=normal>The pay was good, though.

Text.SourceString: The thing about playing the guitar is that you have to feel it in your gut first.//<portrait=normal>Then it will flow out through the melody.
Text.LocalizedString: The thing about playing the guitar is that you have to feel it in your gut first.//<portrait=normal>Then it will flow out through the melody.

Text.SourceString: Feeeeel it, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Feeeeel it, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I met all sorts of folks on the road.//<portrait=happy>This one time, I met this guy with a really thick mustache, and he had a talking hat.//<portrait=normal>Nothing magic about it, though. It was a robot that he built.
Text.LocalizedString: I met all sorts of folks on the road.//<portrait=happy>This one time, I met this guy with a really thick mustache, and he had a talking hat.//<portrait=normal>Nothing magic about it, though. It was a robot that he built.

Text.SourceString: There’s a song in there. I can feel it!
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a song in there. I can feel it!

Text.SourceString: I’m not in the mood for pasta tonight, but I suppose it’s all we’ve got.//<portrait=sad><NPCName>Lily’s</> too busy to run to the store, and I keep forgetting.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not in the mood for pasta tonight, but I suppose it’s all we’ve got.//<portrait=sad><NPCName>Lily’s</> too busy to run to the store, and I keep forgetting.

Text.SourceString: I should pick up some greens for the fridge. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: I should pick up some greens for the fridge. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Should I go to <NPCName>Sam</>’s, or should I just run to the woodland real quick?
Text.LocalizedString: Should I go to <NPCName>Sam</>’s, or should I just run to the woodland real quick?

Text.SourceString: Oh, since I have you here… I have something to ask.//You didn't slide my sis a diamond, did you?//<portrait=annoyed>It wasn’t you, was it?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, since I have you here… I have something to ask.//You didn't slide my sis a diamond, did you?//<portrait=annoyed>It wasn’t you, was it?

Text.SourceString: Ah, never mind then...//My sister was upset the other day because she said that somebody was trying to buy her affection.//She was given a diamond, and she kind of lost it. Poor thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, never mind then...//My sister was upset the other day because she said that somebody was trying to buy her affection.//She was given a diamond, and she kind of lost it. Poor thing.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Lily</> is a bit touchy when it comes to flashy gifts like pearls or gold bars.//<portrait=normal>She’s a sensitive soul.//Now, if you want to get on her good side, give her some kind of food instead.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Lily</> is a bit touchy when it comes to flashy gifts like pearls or gold bars.//<portrait=normal>She’s a sensitive soul.//Now, if you want to get on her good side, give her some kind of food instead.

Text.SourceString: Like what, you ask? Hmm, let's think...//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Lily</> loves pancakes, omurice… Hmm, what else?
Text.LocalizedString: Like what, you ask? Hmm, let's think...//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Lily</> loves pancakes, omurice… Hmm, what else?

Text.SourceString: Laaaaa… laaaaa~ Coral reefs… Coral, coral reefs~ Deep in blue sea… You’re old and pretty~ Laaaaa~//<portrait=blushing>What do you think? Not bad, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Laaaaa… laaaaa~ Coral reefs… Coral, coral reefs~ Deep in blue sea… You’re old and pretty~ Laaaaa~//<portrait=blushing>What do you think? Not bad, huh?

Text.SourceString: …You’re leaving me hanging here, bud…
Text.LocalizedString: …You’re leaving me hanging here, bud…

Text.SourceString: Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>, want to hear my new song? I wrote it yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>, want to hear my new song? I wrote it yesterday.

Text.SourceString: Flowers~ You beautiful flowers~ As beauuuuutiful as the eyes of my love~
Text.LocalizedString: Flowers~ You beautiful flowers~ As beauuuuutiful as the eyes of my love~

Text.SourceString: This is usually the season when a lot of fish eggs hatch.//I had to release a lot of fish back to the ocean the other day because they were too small.
Text.LocalizedString: This is usually the season when a lot of fish eggs hatch.//I had to release a lot of fish back to the ocean the other day because they were too small.

Text.SourceString: Doesn’t all this new life make you feel inspired, <PlayerName>$player</>? The birth of new creatures also means the birth of new ideas.
Text.LocalizedString: Doesn’t all this new life make you feel inspired, <PlayerName>$player</>? The birth of new creatures also means the birth of new ideas.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//I’ve got a couple of new songs I want to play.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//I’ve got a couple of new songs I want to play.

Text.SourceString: You hear that, <PlayerName>$player</>? I only wish I could sing as great as the birds. So carefree and beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: You hear that, <PlayerName>$player</>? I only wish I could sing as great as the birds. So carefree and beautiful.

Text.SourceString: The island is so alive with music, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The crashing of the waves, the chirping of the birds, and even the rustling of the new leaves come together to make this beautiful Spring music.
Text.LocalizedString: The island is so alive with music, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The crashing of the waves, the chirping of the birds, and even the rustling of the new leaves come together to make this beautiful Spring music.

Text.SourceString: It’s so much nicer to go out there and fish now.//I don’t have to stand in the freezing cold anymore.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so much nicer to go out there and fish now.//I don’t have to stand in the freezing cold anymore.

Text.SourceString: I caught a tuna the other day, so I guess we’re entering Summer now.
Text.LocalizedString: I caught a tuna the other day, so I guess we’re entering Summer now.

Text.SourceString: The Summer breeze feels different on my face… A little saltier than Spring, if you want to know.
Text.LocalizedString: The Summer breeze feels different on my face… A little saltier than Spring, if you want to know.

Text.SourceString: I see seals, turtles, all kinds of wild animals swimming to shore in Summer.//<portrait=normal>I talk to them sometimes too, for fun.
Text.LocalizedString: I see seals, turtles, all kinds of wild animals swimming to shore in Summer.//<portrait=normal>I talk to them sometimes too, for fun.

Text.SourceString: The heat’s getting to me, <PlayerName>$player</>. Should I go for a swim?//<portrait=normal>I might if you will too…
Text.LocalizedString: The heat’s getting to me, <PlayerName>$player</>. Should I go for a swim?//<portrait=normal>I might if you will too…

Text.SourceString: Nice cold milk sounds good…but I probably shouldn’t.//It upsets my stomach, and my day’s just begun.
Text.LocalizedString: Nice cold milk sounds good…but I probably shouldn’t.//It upsets my stomach, and my day’s just begun.

Text.SourceString: I wouldn’t sail too far if I were you.//Not in this heat. You might run into a storm at sea… Not saying you would.
Text.LocalizedString: I wouldn’t sail too far if I were you.//Not in this heat. You might run into a storm at sea… Not saying you would.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Sunny</> is the defending champion in the swimming contest. //<portrait=surprised>I don’t understand how he can swim so fast at his age!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Sunny</> is the defending champion in the swimming contest. //<portrait=surprised>I don’t understand how he can swim so fast at his age!

Text.SourceString: Ha! Never really realized how glowing you look in the Summer heat.//It suits you.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha! Never really realized how glowing you look in the Summer heat.//It suits you.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know why all the songs I’m writing are super sad lately. Here’s what I wrote yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know why all the songs I’m writing are super sad lately. Here’s what I wrote yesterday.

Text.SourceString: “The lifeless leaves have left my life.” What a downer.
Text.LocalizedString: “The lifeless leaves have left my life.” What a downer.

Text.SourceString: I’m still singing and writing songs, but it’s harder for me to do in Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m still singing and writing songs, but it’s harder for me to do in Fall.

Text.SourceString: You know how I know it’s Fall? I caught plenty of cod yesterday!
Text.LocalizedString: You know how I know it’s Fall? I caught plenty of cod yesterday!

Text.SourceString: I woke up today, and I didn’t feel too good. Then I looked at the calendar.//This is the week when we lost Mom…
Text.LocalizedString: I woke up today, and I didn’t feel too good. Then I looked at the calendar.//This is the week when we lost Mom…

Text.SourceString: Summer was cool. I caught plenty of tuna. The Beach Shack was pretty happy…//Today is a different story.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer was cool. I caught plenty of tuna. The Beach Shack was pretty happy…//Today is a different story.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a big fan of Fall.//I don’t hate it… It’s all right.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a big fan of Fall.//I don’t hate it… It’s all right.

Text.SourceString: Didn’t catch a lot of fish today, but I still managed to catch a yellowfin tuna. Must be Winter!
Text.LocalizedString: Didn’t catch a lot of fish today, but I still managed to catch a yellowfin tuna. Must be Winter!

Text.SourceString: Are you looking forward to the New Year’s Eve Festival, <PlayerName>$player</>? There’s usually a lot of good food and fun games!//I’ll be singing too… Got some new tunes here in the brain!
Text.LocalizedString: Are you looking forward to the New Year’s Eve Festival, <PlayerName>$player</>? There’s usually a lot of good food and fun games!//I’ll be singing too… Got some new tunes here in the brain!

Text.SourceString: It can be dangerous to go out on the ocean in Winter, but if you’re trained and you’re careful, everything should turn out fine.
Text.LocalizedString: It can be dangerous to go out on the ocean in Winter, but if you’re trained and you’re careful, everything should turn out fine.

Text.SourceString: Is it too cold to eat ice cream? Maybe, but I certainly wouldn’t say no if somebody offered me one!
Text.LocalizedString: Is it too cold to eat ice cream? Maybe, but I certainly wouldn’t say no if somebody offered me one!

Text.SourceString: Some fish don’t stick around in Winter. They go… They swim away to warmer waters.
Text.LocalizedString: Some fish don’t stick around in Winter. They go… They swim away to warmer waters.

Text.SourceString: Like what? Hmm…let’s see. Rainbow fish aren’t Winter fish. They’re Fall.//Cobia too, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: Like what? Hmm…let’s see. Rainbow fish aren’t Winter fish. They’re Fall.//Cobia too, I think.

Text.SourceString: A lot of things happened this past year. Two people and a corporate office moved in.
Text.LocalizedString: A lot of things happened this past year. Two people and a corporate office moved in.

Text.SourceString: I’m just glad that people are seeing the potential in this island.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just glad that people are seeing the potential in this island.

Text.SourceString: I hope this new year gives you a chance for a fresh start, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Whether that means taking another run at your goals or maybe setting some new ones.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope this new year gives you a chance for a fresh start, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Whether that means taking another run at your goals or maybe setting some new ones.

Text.SourceString: Making peace with myself was the hardest thing I’ve ever done.//Now I take every day as it comes, with an extra dose of gratitude.
Text.LocalizedString: Making peace with myself was the hardest thing I’ve ever done.//Now I take every day as it comes, with an extra dose of gratitude.

Text.SourceString: It’s a bit of a tradition for me to bring fresh fish to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//<portrait=happy>My dad would always bring his smoked salmon.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a bit of a tradition for me to bring fresh fish to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//<portrait=happy>My dad would always bring his smoked salmon.

Text.SourceString: And I’ll open the festival with a song of my own.//<portrait=happy>Drives the crowds wild.
Text.LocalizedString: And I’ll open the festival with a song of my own.//<portrait=happy>Drives the crowds wild.

Text.SourceString: *yawns* I’m still tired from singing all day yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: *yawns* I’m still tired from singing all day yesterday.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I’m happy singing here, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I don’t need some fancy label to tell me how to live.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I’m happy singing here, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I don’t need some fancy label to tell me how to live.

Text.SourceString: Today I wanna focus on my soul and just feed my brain some thoughts.
Text.LocalizedString: Today I wanna focus on my soul and just feed my brain some thoughts.

Text.SourceString: My throat feels scratchy…//<portrait=sad>Must be from eating too many banana fritters last night.
Text.LocalizedString: My throat feels scratchy…//<portrait=sad>Must be from eating too many banana fritters last night.

Text.SourceString: Either that, or I’m developing a pollen allergy. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Either that, or I’m developing a pollen allergy. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: One of these days, I’ll go fishing at your farm.//I’m interested in surveying the area to see what kinds of fish swim there.
Text.LocalizedString: One of these days, I’ll go fishing at your farm.//I’m interested in surveying the area to see what kinds of fish swim there.

Text.SourceString: Not today, though. Maybe when the water is a bit cooler.
Text.LocalizedString: Not today, though. Maybe when the water is a bit cooler.

Text.SourceString: Why do I feel like there’s a new bug in town every Summer?
Text.LocalizedString: Why do I feel like there’s a new bug in town every Summer?

Text.SourceString: I could really go for some ice cream right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I could really go for some ice cream right now.

Text.SourceString: I’m taking the day off for the Beach Cleanup Festival so I can participate.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m taking the day off for the Beach Cleanup Festival so I can participate.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been bringing in more trash than usual when I fish. Have you noticed that too?
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been bringing in more trash than usual when I fish. Have you noticed that too?

Text.SourceString: It’s a pity, really. But hopefully, it’ll get better and better every day.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a pity, really. But hopefully, it’ll get better and better every day.

Text.SourceString: The change in the season never really bothers me. I still fish… I still sing.
Text.LocalizedString: The change in the season never really bothers me. I still fish… I still sing.

Text.SourceString: I don’t pay much attention to the calendar. Too constricting.//I usually notice the seasons changing by the type of fish I catch.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t pay much attention to the calendar. Too constricting.//I usually notice the seasons changing by the type of fish I catch.

Text.SourceString: Let’s see what I can come up with for a Fall song.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s see what I can come up with for a Fall song.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be deep in thought.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be deep in thought.]

Text.SourceString: Happy harvest season, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Happy harvest season, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: Oh, hang on… I have Fall melodies coming into my mind. Dum~ Dum~
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hang on… I have Fall melodies coming into my mind. Dum~ Dum~

Text.SourceString: Singing in the rain? Now that is an idea.
Text.LocalizedString: Singing in the rain? Now that is an idea.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how I feel about that. It just seems… Cold.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how I feel about that. It just seems… Cold.

Text.SourceString: Money was never really a thing for me. My dad was a fisher his whole life, and Mom was a diver.//We had a pretty great life overall.
Text.LocalizedString: Money was never really a thing for me. My dad was a fisher his whole life, and Mom was a diver.//We had a pretty great life overall.

Text.SourceString: Growing up, I knew some people who had a lot more than we did, but they weren’t half as happy.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up, I knew some people who had a lot more than we did, but they weren’t half as happy.

Text.SourceString: I almost slipped on the ice this morning. You be careful out there, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: I almost slipped on the ice this morning. You be careful out there, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: One of my favorite things about Winter is all the festive decorations. They make the town feel so alive.
Text.LocalizedString: One of my favorite things about Winter is all the festive decorations. They make the town feel so alive.

Text.SourceString: Making peace with myself was the hardest thing I’ve ever done.//Now I take every day as it comes, with an extra dose of gratitude.
Text.LocalizedString: Making peace with myself was the hardest thing I’ve ever done.//Now I take every day as it comes, with an extra dose of gratitude.

Text.SourceString: I don’t travel a lot. Like, travel for leisure, you know. But I’ve gone places for work, and I’ve seen things.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t travel a lot. Like, travel for leisure, you know. But I’ve gone places for work, and I’ve seen things.

Text.SourceString: I guess being away from my family for too long just isn’t for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess being away from my family for too long just isn’t for me.

Text.SourceString: I’m a bit chilly. Might need to put on a coat.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a bit chilly. Might need to put on a coat.

Text.SourceString: This place has that damp aura about it, and the rain makes it worse.
Text.LocalizedString: This place has that damp aura about it, and the rain makes it worse.

Text.SourceString: My boat isn’t the most reliable in the rain, so I better stick to fishing on sunny days.
Text.LocalizedString: My boat isn’t the most reliable in the rain, so I better stick to fishing on sunny days.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]

Text.SourceString: I’m a bit chilly. Might need to put on a coat.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a bit chilly. Might need to put on a coat.

Text.SourceString: This place has that damp aura about it, and the rain makes it worse.
Text.LocalizedString: This place has that damp aura about it, and the rain makes it worse.

Text.SourceString: My boat isn’t the most reliable in the rain, so I better stick to fishing on sunny days.
Text.LocalizedString: My boat isn’t the most reliable in the rain, so I better stick to fishing on sunny days.

Text.SourceString: It gets dark so early lately.
Text.LocalizedString: It gets dark so early lately.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is in a rush.]

Text.SourceString: One of my favorite things about Winter is all the festive decorations. They make the town feel so alive.
Text.LocalizedString: One of my favorite things about Winter is all the festive decorations. They make the town feel so alive.

Text.SourceString: It gets dark so early lately.
Text.LocalizedString: It gets dark so early lately.

Text.SourceString: It gets dark so fast in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: It gets dark so fast in Winter.

Text.SourceString: What if I write a song about Winter and cheerful bells?//<portrait=happy>Bells jingling and people singing along and laughing.
Text.LocalizedString: What if I write a song about Winter and cheerful bells?//<portrait=happy>Bells jingling and people singing along and laughing.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… Doesn’t ring a bell.//<portrait=annoyed>You sure you got the melody right?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… Doesn’t ring a bell.//<portrait=annoyed>You sure you got the melody right?

Text.SourceString: It gets dark so early lately.
Text.LocalizedString: It gets dark so early lately.

Text.SourceString: I’m in the mood for something crunchy.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m in the mood for something crunchy.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is singing – better not bother him.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Theo</> is singing – better not bother him.]

Text.SourceString: Any song requests, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Any song requests, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: This gig isn’t really banking the big bucks for me. But it isn’t always about the money, ya know?//<portrait=happy>It’s about doing something that you love.
Text.LocalizedString: This gig isn’t really banking the big bucks for me. But it isn’t always about the money, ya know?//<portrait=happy>It’s about doing something that you love.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, are you here for me?//<portrait=surprised>Nah! Just messing with you!//<portrait=happy>Grab a seat, I’m about to sing. You won’t want to miss this.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, are you here for me?//<portrait=surprised>Nah! Just messing with you!//<portrait=happy>Grab a seat, I’m about to sing. You won’t want to miss this.

Text.SourceString: I had this mega satisfying meal that <NpcName>Frank</> made yesterday.//<portrait=normal>Not sure if he's got leftovers, but give it a shot if he does.
Text.LocalizedString: I had this mega satisfying meal that <NpcName>Frank</> made yesterday.//<portrait=normal>Not sure if he's got leftovers, but give it a shot if he does.

Text.SourceString: Oy, <NpcName>Frank</>! Make one of those super meals for <PlayerName>$player</>, will ya?
Text.LocalizedString: Oy, <NpcName>Frank</>! Make one of those super meals for <PlayerName>$player</>, will ya?

Text.SourceString: Yup, here I am. Where else would I be? Born to fish, that's me.
Text.LocalizedString: Yup, here I am. Where else would I be? Born to fish, that's me.

Text.SourceString: I went to the lookout the other day and saw your farm. You’ve done a great job with it, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: I went to the lookout the other day and saw your farm. You’ve done a great job with it, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: I sing to chill out my soul. Hopefully, it hits the same notes for anyone who listens.
Text.LocalizedString: I sing to chill out my soul. Hopefully, it hits the same notes for anyone who listens.

Text.SourceString: I already delivered some of my catch to the Beach Shack.//Aiming to hook a few more before the day's out.
Text.LocalizedString: I already delivered some of my catch to the Beach Shack.//Aiming to hook a few more before the day's out.

Text.SourceString: Day fishing's my jam.//<portrait=normal>Don't need to cast out under the moonlight.
Text.LocalizedString: Day fishing's my jam.//<portrait=normal>Don't need to cast out under the moonlight.

Text.SourceString: You’re welcome to join the meeting here, <PlayerName>$player</>…//<portrait=normal>No pressure.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re welcome to join the meeting here, <PlayerName>$player</>…//<portrait=normal>No pressure.

Text.SourceString: I come here whenever I feel like things are a bit overwhelming.//<portrait=normal>But I also come sometimes just to share something about my day.//Sometimes a little company is all we need.
Text.LocalizedString: I come here whenever I feel like things are a bit overwhelming.//<portrait=normal>But I also come sometimes just to share something about my day.//Sometimes a little company is all we need.

Text.SourceString: Breaking habits is a tough game. But I'm taking it one day at a time.//With the right support system, I believe that any of us can do it.
Text.LocalizedString: Breaking habits is a tough game. But I'm taking it one day at a time.//With the right support system, I believe that any of us can do it.

Text.SourceString: Nothing in life's a walk in the park, <PlayerName>$player</>.//But taking it step by step helps a lot!
Text.LocalizedString: Nothing in life's a walk in the park, <PlayerName>$player</>.//But taking it step by step helps a lot!

Text.SourceString: I’m lucky I got out when I could.//<portrait=sad>I didn’t know what would happen to my family or me if I…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m lucky I got out when I could.//<portrait=sad>I didn’t know what would happen to my family or me if I…

Text.SourceString: Never mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Never mind.

Text.SourceString: Always felt like I was waiting for something. No clue what.//<portrait=sad>It felt like torture.
Text.LocalizedString: Always felt like I was waiting for something. No clue what.//<portrait=sad>It felt like torture.

Text.SourceString: Now I’m not waiting anymore.//<portrait=happy>I’m living…
Text.LocalizedString: Now I’m not waiting anymore.//<portrait=happy>I’m living…

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be concentrating.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Theo</> seems to be concentrating.]

Text.SourceString: Sure are a lot of books in the library…
Text.LocalizedString: Sure are a lot of books in the library…

Text.SourceString: Do you think anyone’s read all these books?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think anyone’s read all these books?

Text.SourceString: I hope you didn’t come here looking for a song, because I’m not here to sing.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you didn’t come here looking for a song, because I’m not here to sing.

Text.SourceString: It’s just raining so hard outside, so…//Um… What was your question?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s just raining so hard outside, so…//Um… What was your question?

Text.SourceString: I really like this positive glow that you bring, <PlayerName>$player</>. Always puts a smile on my face.
Text.LocalizedString: I really like this positive glow that you bring, <PlayerName>$player</>. Always puts a smile on my face.

Text.SourceString: You're mega chill. I appreciate that vibe.
Text.LocalizedString: You're mega chill. I appreciate that vibe.

Text.SourceString: You've got the whole good listener thing down pat.
Text.LocalizedString: You've got the whole good listener thing down pat.

Text.SourceString: It’s not that I don’t want to accept my mother’s death. It’s just…
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not that I don’t want to accept my mother’s death. It’s just…

Text.SourceString: I dunno.
Text.LocalizedString: I dunno.

Text.SourceString: How do you ever fully come to terms with someone being gone for good?
Text.LocalizedString: How do you ever fully come to terms with someone being gone for good?

Text.SourceString: Now all I've got of my mom is what's in my head, it has to be enough, right?//<portrait=sad>But what if it’s not enough? Where else do I look?
Text.LocalizedString: Now all I've got of my mom is what's in my head, it has to be enough, right?//<portrait=sad>But what if it’s not enough? Where else do I look?

Text.SourceString: Dad once said that all any parent ever wants is for their children to be happy.//I think he was right. I think that’s what my mother would’ve wanted for <NpcName>Lily</> and me.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad once said that all any parent ever wants is for their children to be happy.//I think he was right. I think that’s what my mother would’ve wanted for <NpcName>Lily</> and me.

Text.SourceString: Make no mistake, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m going to pursue happiness. I won’t disappoint my mother.
Text.LocalizedString: Make no mistake, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m going to pursue happiness. I won’t disappoint my mother.

Text.SourceString: You must be mad fit, working day in and day out on that big farm.//Teach me your secret sometime, will ya?
Text.LocalizedString: You must be mad fit, working day in and day out on that big farm.//Teach me your secret sometime, will ya?

Text.SourceString: I’m not <NpcName>Theo</> the fisher today. Today I am <NpcName>Theo</>, the singer!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not <NpcName>Theo</> the fisher today. Today I am <NpcName>Theo</>, the singer!

Text.SourceString: Sing a ballad with me, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Sing a ballad with me, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I used to sing to <NpcName>Lily</> all the time when we were kids. She loved it.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to sing to <NpcName>Lily</> all the time when we were kids. She loved it.

Text.SourceString: Ask her! She’ll tell you the same thing. If you can get her to talk to you, that is.//<portrait=sad>She can seem…distant sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Ask her! She’ll tell you the same thing. If you can get her to talk to you, that is.//<portrait=sad>She can seem…distant sometimes.

Text.SourceString: If you ever need a friend, come and find me.//You’re always there for me… I owe you. A lot.
Text.LocalizedString: If you ever need a friend, come and find me.//You’re always there for me… I owe you. A lot.

Text.SourceString: If you need anything done…favor or…<Italic>anything</>… I’m your guy.
Text.LocalizedString: If you need anything done…favor or…<Italic>anything</>… I’m your guy.

Text.SourceString: Ugh… I gave in to temptation and had some milk this morning. I hate myself.//<portrait=angry>Milk doesn’t agree with me. It hurts me.//It’s brought me nothing but pain.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh… I gave in to temptation and had some milk this morning. I hate myself.//<portrait=angry>Milk doesn’t agree with me. It hurts me.//It’s brought me nothing but pain.

Text.SourceString: My stomach hurts.
Text.LocalizedString: My stomach hurts.

Text.SourceString: If I had a keg, I would make strawberry juice all year long and nothing else.//I might just start farming strawberries and do it anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: If I had a keg, I would make strawberry juice all year long and nothing else.//I might just start farming strawberries and do it anyway.

Text.SourceString: Wait a sec… Do you need a keg or a jar to make juice?//<portrait=concerned>Hmm… One of those, anyway. You get what I mean.
Text.LocalizedString: Wait a sec… Do you need a keg or a jar to make juice?//<portrait=concerned>Hmm… One of those, anyway. You get what I mean.

Text.SourceString: How 'bout hanging out with me at the beach sometime?//<portrait=normal>It gets pretty lonely up there… I could use the company.
Text.LocalizedString: How 'bout hanging out with me at the beach sometime?//<portrait=normal>It gets pretty lonely up there… I could use the company.

Text.SourceString: Or you could come over to my house if you prefer… It’s more private.
Text.LocalizedString: Or you could come over to my house if you prefer… It’s more private.

Text.SourceString: I left my window open last night, and a cat sneaked into my bedroom this morning.//I freaked out and jumped out of bed so fast. My head went all fuzzy, and I couldn’t see for a good few seconds.
Text.LocalizedString: I left my window open last night, and a cat sneaked into my bedroom this morning.//I freaked out and jumped out of bed so fast. My head went all fuzzy, and I couldn’t see for a good few seconds.

Text.SourceString: That was really weird! I can still feel my ears popping.
Text.LocalizedString: That was really weird! I can still feel my ears popping.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Lily</> and Dad are everything to me.//<portrait=sad>Ever since Mom passed away, I can’t bear the thought of being away from them.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Lily</> and Dad are everything to me.//<portrait=sad>Ever since Mom passed away, I can’t bear the thought of being away from them.

Text.SourceString: I hate to talk about it, but I guess talking about it is the first step in acknowledging my feelings.//<portrait=normal>Here goes nothing.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate to talk about it, but I guess talking about it is the first step in acknowledging my feelings.//<portrait=normal>Here goes nothing.

Text.SourceString: My heart broke when Dad came home to tell us that Mom had an accident while diving. It still hurts.//I’m afraid this feeling will never go away.
Text.LocalizedString: My heart broke when Dad came home to tell us that Mom had an accident while diving. It still hurts.//I’m afraid this feeling will never go away.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard for me to let Mom go. She was still so young. It just doesn’t feel right, <PlayerName>$player</>.//She had a whole life ahead of her, but she was taken so suddenly. We were just little kids.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard for me to let Mom go. She was still so young. It just doesn’t feel right, <PlayerName>$player</>.//She had a whole life ahead of her, but she was taken so suddenly. We were just little kids.

Text.SourceString: …I never got to say goodbye.
Text.LocalizedString: …I never got to say goodbye.

Text.SourceString: I can think of a way to pay you back…for all your help and the good times I’ve had talking with you.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I could come over to your farm and take care of things for you for a change.
Text.LocalizedString: I can think of a way to pay you back…for all your help and the good times I’ve had talking with you.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I could come over to your farm and take care of things for you for a change.

Text.SourceString: Do a bit of watering or something… What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Do a bit of watering or something… What do you think?

Text.SourceString: You live near <NpcName>Kenny’s</>, right? If you see him, will you tell him to come see me?//I’ve been looking for him all Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: You live near <NpcName>Kenny’s</>, right? If you see him, will you tell him to come see me?//I’ve been looking for him all Summer.

Text.SourceString: Think I found one of his flutes near my place.//I mentioned it to him when I bumped into him at the store, but he hasn't come by to pick it up yet.
Text.LocalizedString: Think I found one of his flutes near my place.//I mentioned it to him when I bumped into him at the store, but he hasn't come by to pick it up yet.

Text.SourceString: Spending too much time in crowds isn’t good for my soul.//It drains my creativity. That’s why I only perform on weekends.
Text.LocalizedString: Spending too much time in crowds isn’t good for my soul.//It drains my creativity. That’s why I only perform on weekends.

Text.SourceString: I like spending time with you.//<portrait=blushing>It energizes me… I wish I could do it more often.
Text.LocalizedString: I like spending time with you.//<portrait=blushing>It energizes me… I wish I could do it more often.

Text.SourceString: Spring is extra pretty with you around.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is extra pretty with you around.

Text.SourceString: Use extra blankets tonight, will you?//I don’t want you to get cold.
Text.LocalizedString: Use extra blankets tonight, will you?//I don’t want you to get cold.

Text.SourceString: Winter isn’t so bad now that you’re around.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter isn’t so bad now that you’re around.

Text.SourceString: I learned to make fish tacos the other day, and they turned out pretty good.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I can make some for you sometime.
Text.LocalizedString: I learned to make fish tacos the other day, and they turned out pretty good.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I can make some for you sometime.

Text.SourceString: Your eyes are flowers~ And your smile is my world~
Text.LocalizedString: Your eyes are flowers~ And your smile is my world~

Text.SourceString: That’s a no, then? I was just trying out a new song, but I wasn’t feeling it either, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s a no, then? I was just trying out a new song, but I wasn’t feeling it either, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: Yeah? You like? I worked so hard on that.//<portrait=happy>I can feel it. This one is going to be a hit.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah? You like? I worked so hard on that.//<portrait=happy>I can feel it. This one is going to be a hit.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad you like it. I was on my boat yesterday, thinking about you, and the song just came to me.//<portrait=happy>You should come over sometime, and I’ll play you the rest.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad you like it. I was on my boat yesterday, thinking about you, and the song just came to me.//<portrait=happy>You should come over sometime, and I’ll play you the rest.

Text.SourceString: Aww, <PlayerName>$player</>. Stop looking at me like that.//You’re making me blush!
Text.LocalizedString: Aww, <PlayerName>$player</>. Stop looking at me like that.//You’re making me blush!

Text.SourceString: My neck feels a bit stiff. Ugh… I guess I slept on it funny last night, but I didn’t think it would last this long.
Text.LocalizedString: My neck feels a bit stiff. Ugh… I guess I slept on it funny last night, but I didn’t think it would last this long.

Text.SourceString: I slept on my stomach.//<portrait=annoyed>Usually, my neck sorts itself out in a couple of hours. Never taken this long before.
Text.LocalizedString: I slept on my stomach.//<portrait=annoyed>Usually, my neck sorts itself out in a couple of hours. Never taken this long before.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry too much if you wake up with a sore neck. It’ll get better in time.//The thing is… Neck is neck. It gets sore once in a while.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry too much if you wake up with a sore neck. It’ll get better in time.//The thing is… Neck is neck. It gets sore once in a while.

Text.SourceString: You look extra cute today!//Spring suits you.
Text.LocalizedString: You look extra cute today!//Spring suits you.

Text.SourceString: You look extra cute today!//Fall looks good on you.
Text.LocalizedString: You look extra cute today!//Fall looks good on you.

Text.SourceString: Sleeping is great… It’s even better when it’s snowing out.//Sleep soothes the mind. It’s an important part of the day.
Text.LocalizedString: Sleeping is great… It’s even better when it’s snowing out.//Sleep soothes the mind. It’s an important part of the day.

Text.SourceString: Thank you for helping me.
Text.LocalizedString: Thank you for helping me.

Text.SourceString: The red boat there, it's more than just a vessel to me. It's my father's legacy.//He spent countless hours on these waters, just like I do now.
Text.LocalizedString: The red boat there, it's more than just a vessel to me. It's my father's legacy.//He spent countless hours on these waters, just like I do now.

Text.SourceString: I remember how proud Dad was when he put those lampions up on the boat. Said it was to light the way home after a long day's catch.//That's what he told me when I was five.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember how proud Dad was when he put those lampions up on the boat. Said it was to light the way home after a long day's catch.//That's what he told me when I was five.

Text.SourceString: Now that I'm an adult, I think he had the lampions up because that's the only decorations we had.//<portrait=sad>Lampions and family pictures, not much else.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that I'm an adult, I think he had the lampions up because that's the only decorations we had.//<portrait=sad>Lampions and family pictures, not much else.

Text.SourceString: I may have given my boat a fresh coat of paint, but that red color is sacred.//<portrait=normal>It's a symbol of our family's history, and I couldn't bear to change it.
Text.LocalizedString: I may have given my boat a fresh coat of paint, but that red color is sacred.//<portrait=normal>It's a symbol of our family's history, and I couldn't bear to change it.

Text.SourceString: There's something about being out here on the open sea, that makes me feel closer to Mom.//<portrait=sad>Like she's still with me in some way.
Text.LocalizedString: There's something about being out here on the open sea, that makes me feel closer to Mom.//<portrait=sad>Like she's still with me in some way.

Text.SourceString: Some folks might say it's just a boat, but to me, it's a piece of who I am.//<portrait=happy>And I plan to pass it down to my kids one day, so they can understand what it means to be a fisherman and carry on our family traditions.
Text.LocalizedString: Some folks might say it's just a boat, but to me, it's a piece of who I am.//<portrait=happy>And I plan to pass it down to my kids one day, so they can understand what it means to be a fisherman and carry on our family traditions.

Text.SourceString: Mom...the ocean claimed her.//<portrait=concerned>But when I sing here, by the shore, I like to believe that somehow, she can hear me.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom...the ocean claimed her.//<portrait=concerned>But when I sing here, by the shore, I like to believe that somehow, she can hear me.

Text.SourceString: I can tell you one thing, <PlayerName>$Player</>: when things get hard and you feel like you can't handle it, try letting go.//<portrait=happy>Believe that, at the end of the day, things will work out as they should.
Text.LocalizedString: I can tell you one thing, <PlayerName>$Player</>: when things get hard and you feel like you can't handle it, try letting go.//<portrait=happy>Believe that, at the end of the day, things will work out as they should.

Text.SourceString: It helped me, and it might help you too.
Text.LocalizedString: It helped me, and it might help you too.

Text.SourceString: You're doing great today, <PlayerName>$Player</>!//Remember that progress, no matter how small, is still progress.
Text.LocalizedString: You're doing great today, <PlayerName>$Player</>!//Remember that progress, no matter how small, is still progress.
